Resource Class

Defined in: src/resource.js:7

addResolver

(
  • resolver
)

Defined in src/resource.js:128

Register resolvers: code that knows how to get resources needed by the runtime. A resolver will be called with four arguments: the absolute manifest of the requester, the resource being requested, and a resolve / reject pair to fulfill a promise.

Parameters:

  • resolver Function

    The resolver to add.

(
  • proto
  • retriever
)

Defined in src/resource.js:141

Register retrievers: code that knows how to load resources needed by the runtime. A retriever will be called with a URL to retrieve with a protocol that it is able to handle.

Parameters:

  • proto String

    The protocol to register for.

  • retriever Function

    The retriever to add.

FirstPromise

(
  • Promises
)
Promise private static

Defined in src/resource.js:79

Return a promise that resolves when the first of an array of promises resolves, or rejects after all promises reject. Can be thought of as the missing 'Promise.any' - race is no good, since early rejections preempt a subsequent resolution.

Parameters:

  • Promises Promise

    to select from

Returns:

Promise:

Promise resolving with a value from arguments.
